eful auto-configuration which could impact testing coverage. I’m also pondering the correct context for binding `@ConfigurationProperties`.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering environment setup**\\n\\nI'm thinking about the environment setup using `StandardEnvironment` and `MapPropertySource`. If I register `SpringAiRetryAutoConfiguration` and refresh the context, conditions from the `@AutoConfiguration` meta should work. The properties could bind using `EnableConfigurationProperties`, which might eliminate the need for boot-test. I should inspect dependencies from `spring-web` and ensure the necessary libraries for testing like `spring-test` for `MockClientHttpResponse`. Also, I'm considering the impacts of optional dependencies and native-image configurations, aiming to keep things concise.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"The artifact is a Spring Boot auto-configuration module whose runtime dependencies are declared optional, so the normal scaffold would only get the target JAR and not the Spring AI retry or Spring Boot auto-configuration APIs needed for meaningful context/bean coverage.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.springframework.ai:spring-ai-retry:2.0.0-RC2\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"SpringAiRetryAutoConfiguration is conditional on org.springframework.ai.retry.RetryUtils and creates RetryTemplate/ResponseErrorHandler behavior using Spring AI retry exceptions and utilities; this dependency is optional in the target POM and is not pulled transitively.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-autoconfigure:4.1.0-RC1\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"The target classes use Spring Boot auto-configuration and configuration-properties annotations; this dependency is optional in the target POM and is required to load the auto-configuration meaningfully in a Spring context.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"No Docker image or external service is needed. Tests should exercise the auto-configuration by loading a Spring context and verifying the RetryTemplate and ResponseErrorHandler beans plus spring.ai.retry.* property binding. If executing retry behavior rather than only checking bean creation/error handling, configure very small retry/backoff values in the test context, for example max attempts of 2 and an initial interval around 1ms, to avoid slow tests.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The artifact is tied to Spring Boot 4.1.0-RC1 and Spring Framework 7.0.x; dependency version drift could cause classpath conflicts.\",\n    \"Using only direct class instantiation would miss the auto-configuration and configuration-properties behavior that this artifact primarily provides.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0c2b555a41494ec4016a3f37386b088193acde01aa66d636a9\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 3112, "output": 1460, "cacheRead": 27136, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 31708, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782527783153, "responseId": "resp_0c2b555a41494ec4016a3f3727b3d48193a5b1ddb7e7a053d8"}, "toolResults": []}
